The paper deals with the analysis of polynomial threshold functions (PTFs) and their sensitivity, which are topics that are commonly studied in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT), probability theory (cs.PR), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) to obtain its results. Additionally, the paper discusses agnostic learning algorithms for PTFs, which is a topic that falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
